# TRACE EM - Project "Everything" File
This document outlines the responsibilities of every file in the project.

---

## 🚀 Core & Setup
*   **`lib/main.dart`**: The main entry point of the Flutter application. Initializes Firebase, loads environmental variables, configures location services, and starts the background tracking service.
*   **`lib/injection_container.dart`**: Handles Dependency Injection (using GetIt). Links interfaces (Repositories) and UseCases to their actual implementations (Firebase, etc.).
*   **`lib/firebase_options.dart`**: Auto-generated configuration that connects the Flutter app to the Firebase project.
*   **.env**: Stores sensitive configuration like Firebase API Keys, project IDs, and the **`BACKEND_URL`** for the tracking API.
*   **pubspec.yaml**: Lists all Flutter dependencies and project assets (images, fonts).
*   **`lib/core/error/failures.dart`**: App-wide failure and exception classes.

## 🔐 Authentication (Login & Register)
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/splash_screen.dart`**: The initial load screen. Handles auto-login by checking authentication state before deciding whether to show login or home.
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/login_screen.dart`**: A unified screen handling both Login and Registration. Features logic for form submission and "Enter" key trigger support.
*   **`lib/presentation/widgets/auth/auth_widgets.dart`**: Contains reusable UI components for authentication, including custom text fields with floating labels.
*   **`lib/infrastructure/repositories/auth_repository_impl.dart`**: Logic for talking to **Firebase Auth** and **Cloud Firestore** for user management, including the fully implemented **Logout** process.
*   **`lib/domain/repositories/auth_repository.dart`**: Interface for the Auth Repository.
*   **`lib/domain/entities/user_entity.dart`**: Defines the "User" model, including phone number support and region detection metadata.
*   **`lib/domain/usecases/...`** (`check_auth_usecase.dart`, `login_usecase.dart`, `logout_usecase.dart`, `signup_usecase.dart`): Clean Architecture use cases defining specific authentication-related tasks.

## 🏠 Home & Main Dashboard
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/home_screen.dart`**: The central hub using a `BlocBuilder` to provide real-time user data updates. Includes a **Dynamic Notification Badge** on the bell icon alerting users to admin responses, and a Floating Action Button for reports.
*   **`lib/presentation/widgets/home/book_view.dart`**: The "Book" tab. Features a dynamic **Shrinking Map Animation**. Integrates **OpenStreetMap** with **Nominatim** for address searching. Uses **OSRM API** for road-snapped routes. Includes the **Mock Ride Booking Flow**:
    *   **Waiting Dialog**: A 10-second simulated search for nearby drivers.
    *   **Random Driver Picking**: Randomly selects from Motorcycle/Taxi driver pools with unique ratings and vehicle info.
    *   **Virtual Receipt**: Displays details, a map snippet, and a **Doodle Profile Picture** (via Robohash).
    *   **Simulate Drive**: Animates the vehicle icon moving slowly along the route before arriving at the destination.
*   **`lib/presentation/widgets/home/profile_view.dart`**: A premium profile editor that synchronizes directly with the database. Supports updating name, email, phone, address, and maps.
*   **`lib/presentation/widgets/home/track_view.dart`**: The "Track" tab UI for viewing active delivery orders.
*   **`lib/presentation/widgets/home/bottom_nav.dart`**: Custom styled bottom navigation.
*   **`lib/presentation/widgets/curve_painter.dart`**: Custom painter responsible for special UI curves used around the app.

## 📍 Real-Time Tracking & Maps
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/order_tracking_screen.dart`**: Shows the **Live Map** (powered by `flutter_map` and OpenStreetMap) with moving driver updates polled from the backend.
*   **`lib/presentation/widgets/common/region_selector.dart`**: A widget for displaying the current detected region and allowing manual region selection via a dialog.
*   **`lib/core/config/philippine_regions.dart`**: Database of GPS coordinates and boundaries for Philippine regions to center the map automatically.
*   **`lib/core/services/location_service.dart`**: Requests GPS permissions and performs reverse-geocoding to detect the user's current region using Geolocator.
*   **`lib/infrastructure/services/tracking_service.dart`**: A background service that ensures location tracking continues even if the app is minimized. Dynamically links GPS data to the authenticated **Firebase UID** and periodically sends it to the configured backend server.

## 📦 Domain & Business Logic (UseCases, BLoC)
*   **`lib/domain/entities/order_entity.dart`**: Data model representing an order/trace.
*   **`lib/domain/usecases/get_orders_usecase.dart`**: Clean architecture usecase for retrieving order data. 
*   **`lib/domain/usecases/update_profile_usecase.dart`**: Clean architecture usecase for securely updating user profile data.
*   **`lib/presentation/bloc/auth_bloc.dart`** (and `auth_event.dart`, `auth_state.dart`): Manages authentication state (Logged In, Logged Out, Loading, Error).
*   **`lib/presentation/bloc/order_bloc.dart`** (and `order_event.dart`, `order_state.dart`): Manages the state of orders fetching and tracking.

## 📁 Database & Infrastructure
*   **`lib/domain/repositories/order_repository.dart`**: Interface for the Order Repository.
*   **`lib/infrastructure/repositories/order_repository_impl.dart`**: Manages all **Cloud Firestore** interactions for orders, history, and status updates. Live tracking of `isOnline` status.
*   **`android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml`**: Project-level configuration for Android, including core permissions like location tracking and background execution.
*   **`web/index.html`**: Web-level entry point containing document structure for the web build.

## 🛠️ Testing & Debugging
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/debug_control_screen.dart`**: A developer-only panel for simulating orders, moving drivers, and testing the tracking system without real GPS movement.

## 👑 Admin Side (Web/Desktop Layout)
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/admin/admin_home_screen.dart`**: The main dashboard for administrators. Optimized for large screens with a sidebar navigation system.
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/admin/users_page.dart`**: Allows admins to monitor all registered users and their real-time online/offline status in a tabular format.
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/admin/complaints_page.dart`**: A feedback management system where admins can review user reports and provide official responses.
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/admin/orders_management_page.dart`**: Dashboard section tailored for overseeing all global system orders.
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/admin/receipts_page.dart`**: Admin log for tracking ride history, order IDs, and payment details.
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/admin/ratings_page.dart`**: Admin log for monitoring driver performance and user feedback/ratings.
    
## 📋 User Engagement & Feedback
*   **`lib/domain/entities/complaint_entity.dart`**: The data model for user feedback, tracking descriptions, status (pending/resolved), and admin responses.
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/user_reports_screen.dart`**: Dedicated screen for standard users to view their submitted reports and corresponding admin interactions.
*   **`lib/presentation/widgets/home/notifications_view.dart`**: The interactive notification center. Features **clickable notification tiles** that open a mini pop-up dialog.
*   **`lib/presentation/screens/rating_screen.dart`**: Post-ride feedback screen where users can rate drivers and leave comments.

## 🐍 Backend API (Python)
*   **`backend/main.py`**: The **FastAPI** tracking engine. Receives real-time GPS coordinates from logged-in users and serves tracking data for the map interface.
*   **`backend/requirements.txt`**: Lists Python dependencies for the tracking backend.



